Food, raw, culinary fad 970911191551
[1
From: Robert Atmar <ratmar@bcm.tmc.edu>
Date: Fri, 12 Sep 1997 11:02:38 -0500
The moderator listed hepatitis A and C as causes of foodborne viral
illnesses. While hepatitis A can be foodborne, hepatitis C is not.
Hepatitis E is the other hepatitis virus that is enterically transmitted.
In addition, you left out what is probably the most significant group of
viruses associated with contaminated food: Norwalk virus and other related
human caliciviruses (also called SRSVs - small, round, structured viruses).
--
Robert L. Atmar, M.D.
Baylor College of Medicine
Houston, TX
email: ratmar@bcm.tmc.edu
