[2
From: julieb@lava.net
Date: Thu, 11 Sep 1997 18:18:26 -0400
Oh, this is going to produce a virtual "flood" of mail on this subject, and
many of the concerns are justified, however it is important to remember
that tuna "maguro" in Japanese and "ahi" in Hawaiian is a pellagic (open
ocean) species and not subject to the parasites which infest fresh-water
species. However, anyone who eats raw fresh-water fish is playing "parasite
roulette". And of course, unless you're sure the fish has been prepared
carefully, there is no guarantee that your expensive dinner won't be
contaminated with harmful bacteria....they're free.
--
Julie Beardsley
Research analyst
HMSA
Honolulu, Hawaii
julieb@lava.net
